{"legislative_session": "20252026", "identifier": "AB2342", "title": "Parole.", "from_organization": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["bill"], "subject": ["Parole"], "abstracts": [{"note": "summary", "abstract": "The California Constitution authorizes the Governor to affirm, modify, or reverse the decision of the Board of Parole Hearings with respect to the granting, denial, revocation, or suspension of parole of a person sentenced to an indeterminate term upon conviction of murder. Existing law classifies certain felonies as violent felonies for purposes of various provisions of the Penal Code.\n\nThis bill would additionally authorize the Governor to reverse or modify the decision of the board to grant parole to an inmate sentenced for conviction of a violent felony to an indeterminate prison term, as specified, or to a determinate prison term, as specified, if the board's decision is to grant the inmate parole pursuant to the Elderly Parole Program or youth offender parole program.\n\nThese provisions would become operative only if Assembly Constitutional Amendment ____ of the 2025\u201326 Regular Session is approved by the voters at the November 3, 2026, statewide election."}], "other_titles": [{"note": "", "title": "Housing development: transit-oriented development."}], "other_identifiers": [{"identifier": "ocd-bill-ca-20252026-ab2342"}], "actions": [{"description": "Read first time. To print.", "date": "2026-02-19", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["reading-1"], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "From printer. May be heard in committee March 22.", "date": "2026-02-20", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": [], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "Referred to Com. on PUB. S.", "date": "2026-03-16", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["referral-committee"], "related_entities": [{"name": "Com. on PUB. S.", "entity_typ